   <note>A letter written by the Glass, a chief of the Cherokee tribe, to Governor Blount. Glass reveals Colonel Robertson told him about fighting between his tribe and Tennesseans about the impending Treaty at Nashville. He asks that Blount prevent people from coming onto Cherokee land and from threatening Cherokees. The Glass urges peace and honesty in the future.</note>
